		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Burynaibane&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Ouch.<br /><br />Some really good contect in there, but your post is just painful to read!&nbsp;&nbsp;(This isn't a flame, but try using small paragraphs, or something.  (If it makes you feel any better, you got a good rating for the contect!  :)  )<br /><br /><li><b>Partnering:</b><br />Always good.  You make friends.  You kill quicker.  You don't die so fast, when something goes wrong.  What more could you ask for?<br />And rogues <b>are</b> great partners for necros.  It's a shame they're so rare!  The only thing here, is it takes quite a lot of trust in the necro, from the rogue.  (If fear breaks, the rogue will be chewed up pretty fast.  So you want him to be sure you will look after him!)<br /><br /><li><b>Research:</b><br />This is the bane of my existance!  (No pun!)  Oh, how I hate research.  But, yes, if you're dilligent, you can have all the words you need.  Or indeed, you can buy the completed spell, before you need it.<br /><br /><li><b>GM events:</b><br />In my experience, these seem to involve letting something big loose in an area full of people who can't stay alive in it's presence.  And they're rare too!  (I missed the Halloween stuff, though I know it was a little different.)  I don't know If I'd agree with the whole idea of attending them all.  I know lots of people avoid them like the plague!  It's a personal choice thing, I guess.<br /><br />Anyhow...<br /><br />Burynaibane.<br /></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />"If I cannot be a hero, then I shall be a villain!"</td></td></tr><tr><td